						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#128;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#158;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#149;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#162; (Da Mafia) is a crime game from Japan, with players concealing their gangster cards to control the city.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game works as a worker placement game, but the workers are cards for the different gang members; Bosses, Members, Hitman, and Bodyguards. Each player is the head of their gang and places their initial four cards face-down around the city. When they are turned, they might control that section, and gain benefits such as recruiting more gangsters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But before cards are turned up, players have a chance to guess who is concealed where in the city. If they are correct, the player outsmarts the opponent ands gains an advantage.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has their own board for their gangster head, which shows their abilities, recruitment, and player levels and score. The other side is the same but with a special unique ability, meaning players can play a simpler or more complex game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After five rounds, the player who has gained the most notoriety in the city wins the game.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
